  "body": "<!-- Have you done the following? -->\n<!--   * read the Code of Conduct? By filing an Issue, you are expected to -->  \n<!--     comply with it, including treating everyone with respect: -->\n<!--     https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md -->\n<!--   * Reproduced the issue in the latest version of the software -->\n<!--   * Read the debugging docs: https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/stable/HowTo/Monitor/Logging/ -->\n<!--   * Duplicate Issue check:  https://github.com/search?q=+is%3Aissue+repo%3Ahyperledger/Besu -->\n<!-- Note:  Not all sections will apply to all issue types. -->\n\n### Description\nSome merge transition specific callbacks are needlessly execution on forkchoiceUpdate, e.g.\n* stopping BlockPropagationManager\n* setting finalized flag in MergePeerFilter\n\nFor these one-time transition type events, we should implement an unsubscribe behavior for implementations of ForkchoiceUpdatedListener.\n\nrelates to #4265\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n* add the ability to unsubscribe from newForkchoiceUpdated events\n* make blockPropagation\n\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\n1. run or sync a besu client through the merge transition\n2. observe subsequent forkchoiceUpdated call transition-specific methods \n\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\nability to unsubscribe and stop executing callbacks that should stop post-merge or post-finalization\n\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\n\n**Frequency:** [What percentage of the time does it occur?]\n100%\n\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\n* Software version: 22.7.0\n",
